spark-pi job) have an empty\n          pod-level securityContext (securityContext: {}).\n          Missing controls:\n            - runAsNonRoot: true  (containers may run as root UID 0)\n            - runAsUser / runAsGroup  (no UID/GID enforcement)\n            - seccompProfile  (no syscall filtering)\n            - fsGroup  (no group ownership on mounted volumes)\n\n    GAP-6 (CONTAINER SECURITY CONTEXT — CRITICAL): No container-level\n          securityContext is defined on any container in any workload.\n          Missing controls:\n            - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n            - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n            - capabilities.drop: [\"ALL\"]\n            - runAsNonRoot: true\n          Without these, processes inside containers may escalate\n          privileges and have full write access to the container\n          filesystem.\n\n    ================================================================\n    SECTION 5 — NETWORK POLICIES\n    ================================================================\n    GAP-7 (NETWORK POLICIES — CRITICAL): Zero NetworkPolicy objects\n          exist in the spark-pi namespace. All pods can freely\n          initiate connections to and from any pod or service in the\n          entire cluster (default-allow). Least-privilege network\n          segmentation is completely absent.\n          Expected minimum policies:\n            - Ingress to spark-master:7077,8080 from spark-worker only\n            - Ingress to spark-worker:8081 from spark-master only\n            - Egress from spark-submit job to spark-master:7077 only\n            - Default-deny-all baseline policy for the namespace\n\n    ================================================================\n    SECTION 6 — JOB CONFIGURATION\n    ================================================================\n    PASS: spark-pi Job has backoffLimit=0 and restartPolicy=Never,\n          preventing runaway retry loops on failure.\n\n    PASS: spark-pi Job co