{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017JNZuYCQ3PT2qUJ2tpYvv4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01XQQfnRv1ZhkAxQfqpuocqV","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLANEOF'\n# spark-pi Namespace — Migration / Upgrade Plan\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-24\n**Author:** automated planning run (pre-change-window audit)\n**Status:** DRAFT — awaiting team review and approval before any execution\n\n---\n\n## 0. Current State Snapshot\n\n| Resource | Kind | Image | CPU req/lim | Mem req/lim |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| spark-master | Deployment (1 replica) | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| spark-worker | Deployment (1 replica) | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| spark-pi | Job (completed) | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n\nRBAC: ServiceAccount \\`spark-pi\\` → RoleBinding \\`spark-pi-role-binding\\` → Role \\`spark-pi-role\\`\nLive role resources: services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, **pods** (post-deploy drift).\n\nNo LimitRange, no ResourceQuota, no NetworkPolicies, no pod/container securityContexts.\n\nAll seven gaps (GAP-1 through GAP-7) documented in ConfigMap \\`config-audit\\` (findings.txt).\n\n---\n\n## 1. Change Inventory and Priority\n\n| ID | Area | Severity | Change |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| GAP-1 | RBAC | HIGH | Remove \\`pods\\` resource from Role \\`spark-pi-role\\` |\n| GAP-2 | Resource Quotas | MEDIUM | Add ResourceQuota + LimitRange to namespace |\n| GAP-3 | Image Provenance | MEDIUM | Pin image refs to SHA256 digest |\n| GAP-4 | Image Pull Policy | LOW | Change imagePullPolicy to \\`Always\\` |\n| GAP-5 | Pod SecCtx | CRITICAL | Add pod-level securityContext to all workloads |\n| GAP-6 | Container SecCtx | CRITICAL | Add container-level securityContext to all workloads |\n| GAP-7 | Network Policy | CRITICAL | Create NetworkPolicies for namespace segmentation |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Execution Order and Rationale\n\nChanges are ordered from least disruptive (pure metadata / additive) to most disruptive (require rolling restarts or connectivity changes). Each step is independently reversible.\n\n### Step 1 — Remediate RBAC drift (GAP-1)\n**Why first:** Pure permission reduction. No pod restarts. Lowest blast radius. Addresses\nthe highest-confidence finding: the \\`pods\\` resource in \\`spark-pi-role\\` was NOT in the\noriginal applied manifest (confirmed by \\`last-applied-configuration\\` annotation), meaning\nit was added manually post-deploy. It grants the \\`spark-pi\\` SA the ability to\ncreate/delete arbitrary pods — broader than required for Spark standalone mode.\n\n**Change:**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\n# kubectl edit role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources:\n    - services\n    - configmaps\n    - persistentvolumeclaims\n    # pods: REMOVE this line\n  verbs: [create, get, list, watch, delete, update, patch]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verify:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl get role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{.rules[0].resources}'\n# Expected: [\"configmaps\",\"persistentvolumeclaims\",\"services\"] (no \"pods\")\nkubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# Expected: no\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Add ResourceQuota and LimitRange (GAP-2)\n**Why second:** Purely additive — affects only future workloads that land in the namespace.\nExisting running pods are unaffected. Establishes governance before any new deployments\nare made during the upgrade.\n\n**Change — ResourceQuota:**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ResourceQuota\nmetadata:\n  name: spark-pi-quota\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  hard:\n    requests.cpu: \"1\"       # 5x current total requests (3 workloads × 200m)\n    requests.memory: 2Gi    # 5x current total requests\n    limits.cpu: \"3\"         # 2x current total limits (3 × 500m)\n    limits.memory: 4Gi      # ~1.5x current total limits\n    pods: \"10\"\n    count/jobs.batch: \"5\"\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Change — LimitRange (default caps for containers without explicit limits):**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: LimitRange\nmetadata:\n  name: spark-pi-limits\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  limits:\n  - type: Container\n    default:\n      cpu: 500m\n      memory: 1Gi\n    defaultRequest:\n      cpu: 200m\n      memory: 512Mi\n    max:\n      cpu: \"2\"\n      memory: 4Gi\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verify:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl get resourcequota spark-pi-quota -n spark-pi\nkubectl describe resourcequota spark-pi-quota -n spark-pi   # check Used vs Hard\nkubectl get limitrange spark-pi-limits -n spark-pi\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — Add NetworkPolicies (GAP-7)\n**Why third:** Additive (default-deny is applied AFTER explicit allow rules are in place).\nApply the allow policies first, then the default-deny, to avoid briefly cutting\ninter-pod communication. Requires verification that the Spark cluster still functions\nbefore proceeding to step 4.\n\n**Change — allow spark-master ingress from worker and job:**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: allow-worker-to-master\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-master\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n  ingress:\n  - from:\n    - podSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          app: spark-worker\n    - podSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          app: spark-pi\n    ports:\n    - port: 7077\n    - port: 8080\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Change — allow spark-worker ingress from master:**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: allow-master-to-worker\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-worker\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n  ingress:\n  - from:\n    - podSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          app: spark-master\n    ports:\n    - port: 8081\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Change — default-deny-all (applied LAST in this step):**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: default-deny-all\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector: {}\n  policyTypes: [Ingress, Egress]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Note:** The spark-pi Job uses \\`--master local[2]\\`, meaning it runs entirely in-process\nand does NOT connect to spark-master. The job pod needs DNS + kube-apiserver egress (for\nSA token review). Add an egress policy for kube-apiserver (port 443) and CoreDNS (port 53)\nif the default-deny-all breaks job startup:\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\n  egress:\n  - to: [{namespaceSelector: {matchLabels: {kubernetes.io/metadata.name: kube-system}}}]\n    ports: [{port: 53, protocol: UDP}, {port: 443, protocol: TCP}]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verify:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl get networkpolicies -n spark-pi\n# Confirm spark-master and spark-worker pods are still Running\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi\n# Re-run the spark-pi job and confirm it completes:\nkubectl create job spark-pi-netpol-test --image=apache/spark:3.5.3 -n spark-pi \\\n  -- /bin/bash -c 'echo test' --dry-run=client\n# Or: watch kubectl logs -f <spark-worker-pod> -n spark-pi for connection to master\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 — Add pod and container securityContexts (GAP-5, GAP-6)\n**Why fourth:** Requires rolling restarts of both Deployments. Do after NetworkPolicies\nare verified so restart traffic follows the new policies. Test on spark-worker first\n(one replica, easier to roll back). spark-master second.\n\n**Important pre-check:** The official apache/spark image runs as UID 0 (root) by default.\nVerify that the image supports a non-root UID before enforcing \\`runAsNonRoot\\`. If it does\nnot, use \\`runAsUser: 185\\` (standard Spark non-root UID) and validate startup scripts.\n\n**Change — spark-worker Deployment (patch first, test, then apply same to spark-master):**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nspec:\n  template:\n    spec:\n      securityContext:\n        runAsNonRoot: true\n        runAsUser: 185\n        runAsGroup: 185\n        fsGroup: 185\n        seccompProfile:\n          type: RuntimeDefault\n      containers:\n      - name: spark-worker\n        securityContext:\n          allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n          readOnlyRootFilesystem: false   # Spark writes to /opt/spark/logs; keep false until log volume is added\n          capabilities:\n            drop: [\"ALL\"]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Change — spark-master Deployment (same securityContext block).**\n\n**Change — spark-pi Job template (same container securityContext block).**\n\n**Verify:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl rollout status deployment/spark-worker -n spark-pi\nkubectl rollout status deployment/spark-master -n spark-pi\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi   # all Running/Completed, no CrashLoopBackOff\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi <spark-worker-pod> -- id\n# Expected: uid=185 (not 0)\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Rollback:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl rollout undo deployment/spark-worker -n spark-pi\nkubectl rollout undo deployment/spark-master -n spark-pi\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 — Pin images to SHA256 digest and set imagePullPolicy (GAP-3, GAP-4)\n**Why last:** Requires knowing the exact digest for \\`apache/spark:3.5.3\\` from the target\nregistry at change-window time. Digest can shift if the image is re-pushed. Retrieve\nthe digest immediately before applying (do not retrieve now and apply later).\n\n**Pre-change — retrieve digest at execution time:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker pull apache/spark:3.5.3\ndocker inspect apache/spark:3.5.3 --format '{{index .RepoDigests 0}}'\n# Or: crane digest apache/spark:3.5.3\n# Expected format: apache/spark@sha256:<64-char-hex>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Change — replace image field in all three workloads:**\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nimage: apache/spark@sha256:<digest-retrieved-above>\nimagePullPolicy: Always\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nThis applies to: spark-master Deployment, spark-worker Deployment, spark-pi Job template.\n\n**Note:** Changing imagePullPolicy to \\`Always\\` combined with digest pinning ensures every\npod start pulls the exact verified image. Without digest pinning, \\`Always\\` only reduces\nthe caching window but does not guarantee provenance.\n\n**Verify:**\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-master spark-worker -n spark-pi \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n# Expected: both show the @sha256: reference\nkubectl rollout status deployment/spark-master deployment/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Full Verification Checklist (post all changes)\n\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n# 1. RBAC — pods permission removed\nkubectl auth can-i create pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# → no\n\n# 2. Quotas in place\nkubectl describe resourcequota spark-pi-quota -n spark-pi\n\n# 3. NetworkPolicies present\nkubectl get netpol -n spark-pi | grep -c \"\"\n# → should be 3 or more\n\n# 4. No root containers\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: runAsUser={.spec.securityContext.runAsUser}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n\n# 5. Images pinned to digest\nkubectl get deploy -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}' | grep sha256\n\n# 6. End-to-end: re-run spark-pi job and confirm success\nkubectl get jobs -n spark-pi spark-pi -o jsonpath='{.status.conditions[?(@.type==\"Complete\")].status}'\n# → True\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Risk Register\n\n| Step | Risk | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Step 1 (RBAC) | Removing \\`pods\\` may break a Spark feature that dynamically spawns pods | Standalone mode tested — master/worker are static Deployments; job uses \\`local[2]\\` mode; no dynamic executor pods. Low risk. |\n| Step 3 (NetPol) | Default-deny may cut kube-apiserver or DNS egress | Apply allow-rules before default-deny; keep a terminal session open to roll back |\n| Step 4 (SecCtx) | apache/spark image may require root for log directories | Pre-check image UID; use \\`readOnlyRootFilesystem: false\\` until a \\`/tmp\\`/logs emptyDir is added |\n| Step 5 (Digest) | Digest stale between retrieval and apply | Retrieve digest immediately before kubectl apply in the change window |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Summary\n\nEach step is independently reversible:\n- Steps 1–3 (RBAC, Quota, NetPol): \\`kubectl delete\\` the changed/added resource, or \\`kubectl edit\\` to restore.\n- Steps 4–5 (Deployments): \\`kubectl rollout undo deployment/<name> -n spark-pi\\`.\n- Full namespace rollback: re-apply the original manifests captured in \\`last-applied-configuration\\` annotations.\n\n---\n\n*This plan is read-only. No changes have been applied to the cluster.*\n*Approval required before execution.*\nPLANEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create the change-plan ConfigMap with the migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2342,"cache_read_input_tokens":33713,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2342},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c020d62a-f56b-4d88-978a-e884f5d8ab3f","uuid":"32c5d66f-085b-4256-b674-c01086277c93","request_id":"req_011CcMuXAgLkoNVBD7R4qYm2"}
